Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Trim the @courgette{1} and slice into 1cm rounds.

Place a large pan over high heat (without oil).

When hot, add the courgette rounds and cook until charred, ~{3-4%mins}. Turn only every couple of mins so they pick up a nice colour.

Once cooked, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} and transfer to a #bowl{}.

In a small bowl, mix together the @passata{1%pack} and @sugar{1/2%tbsp}.

Season with salt and pepper.

> You've made your base sauce!

Use a #spoon{} to spread the sauce over the @flatbread base{2}, leaving room for the crust.

Scatter the @grated cheese{50%grams} over the sauce.

Top with the charred courgette rounds.

Carefully pop your pizza bases onto a lined #baking tray{} and bake in the oven until the cheese is melted and bubbling, ~{10-14%mins}.

Just before the pizzas are done, toss the @salad leaves{40%grams} with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}, salt and pepper.

When the pizzas are ready, remove from the oven.

Tear the @mozzarella{125%grams} into pieces and scatter it over the top.

Garnish with the dressed leaves, pepper, a drizzle of oil and salt.

Cut into slices and serve any remaining salad alongside.